# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Wheel of Fortune — each player discards hand, draws 7 (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-395 closed Wheel of Fortune as WORKING but carried NO scripted
# puzzle with semantic assertions (the pre-existing wheel_of_fortune_each_player.pzl
# is golden-log-only with no [assertions], heuristic-driven). This audit puzzle
# SCRIPTS the cast and asserts the symmetric hand-refill.
#
# Wheel of Fortune is {2}{R} sorcery: "Each player discards their hand, then
# draws seven cards." (SP$ Discard Mode$ Hand Defined$ Player -> DB$ Draw
# Defined$ Player NumCards$ 7). Two chained effects applied to EVERY player.
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-395):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {2}{R} sorcery (spell cast assertion).
#   2. Defined$ Player (= each player) symmetric discard: both players' starting
#      hands are emptied to the graveyard.
#   3. Chained draw-7 for EACH player: both players end with a refilled hand.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Wheel of Fortune + 2 junk cards in hand (Forest;Forest), 3 Mountains to
#     pay {2}{R}, a deep library to draw 7 from.
#   - P1: 2 junk cards in hand (Plains;Plains), a deep library.
#   - Both players are scripted to PASS after the cast so they do not play lands
#     out of hand (which would shrink the hand count). They still draw on their
#     own turns (only grows the count), so the `ge 7` lower bounds hold durably.
#
# After Wheel resolves: P0 discarded its 2 junk cards (Wheel itself is on the
# stack / heads to graveyard) and drew 7; P1 discarded its 2 junk cards and drew
# 7. Both hands end at >= 7.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Wheel of Fortune Refills Both Hands
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Wheel of Fortune ({2}{R} sorcery). Each player discards their hand and draws 7. Both players' starting junk hands go to the graveyard and both refill to 7+ cards; Wheel itself lands in P0's graveyard. Backs issue mtg-395 (Discard Mode$ Hand + chained Draw 7, Defined$ Player = symmetric).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Wheel of Fortune;Forest;Forest
p0battlefield=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain
p0library=Island;Island;Island;Island;Island;Island;Island;Island;Island;Island

p1life=20
p1hand=Plains;Plains
p1battlefield=
p1library=Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp

[p0_script]
# Cast Wheel of Fortune, then pass for the rest of the game (do not play lands,
# which would shrink the refilled hand).
cast Wheel of Fortune
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[p1_script]
# P1 takes no proactive action.
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[assertions]
# The draw-7 sorcery was actually cast.
spell cast Wheel of Fortune
# Wheel of Fortune itself is in P0's graveyard after resolving (sorcery -> GY).
graveyard contains Wheel of Fortune
# Each player drew seven: both hands refilled to at least 7 (durable lower
# bound — later draw steps only add cards; neither player plays cards out).
hand count ge 7
opponent hand count ge 7
